title: Rust panics with "no entry found for key" when documenting item with conflicting glob import

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Running `cargo +stable doc` fails with ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', src/librustdoc/passes/collect_intra_doc_links.rs:989:16 ``` This is reproducible. The `pub use` is significant, a simple `use` does not trigger the error. The function name `read` is also significant. Naming it `copy` or `read_dir`, both functions existing in `tokio::fs` does *not* trigger the error. This still fails with current nighly versions. ### Code ```Rust pub use tokio::fs::*; fn read() {} ``` ```toml tokio.default-features = false tokio.version = "1.17" tokio.features = ["fs"] ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0 (7737e0b5c 2022-04-04) binary: rustc commit-hash: 7737e0b5c4103216d6fd8cf941b7ab9bdbaace7c commit-date: 2022-04-04 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.60.0 LLVM version: 14.0.0 ``` ``` cargo 1.62.0-nightly (a44758ac8 2022-05-04) release: 1.62.0-nightly commit-hash: a44758ac805600edbb6ba51e7e6fb81a6077c0cd commit-date: 2022-05-04 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu libgit2: 1.4.2 (sys:0.14.2 vendored) libcurl: 7.80.0-DEV (sys:0.4.51+curl-7.80.0 vendored ssl:OpenSSL/1.1.1n) os: Ubuntu 20.04 (focal) [64-bit] ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.62.0-nightly (6dd68402c 2022-05-11) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: end of query stack error: could not document `misc_utils` ```
